modules.description: Encodes and decodes strings using the WTF-8 encoding, which handles unpaired surrogates and ill-formed UTF-8 sequences. Processes byte sequences and string values, preserving invalid code points that standard UTF-8 would reject. Useful for parsing or generating data that includes malformed Unicode, such as certain legacy or corrupted text sources.

Processes UTF-8 encoded strings by folding over code points with a custom function, allowing incremental buffer construction from code points. Operates on strings and buffers, using a codepoint type to represent individual Unicode characters. Enables efficient encoding of code points into a buffer during text processing tasks.
